    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/mesh-independence-study",
    "type": "VerificationActivity",
    "name": "Mesh Independence Study for VAD CFD Model",
    "description": "A systematic mesh independence study was conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry under VAD operating conditions. Three mesh densities (coarse: 2.1M cells, medium: 6.4M cells, fine: 18.7M cells) were evaluated. Grid convergence index (GCI) was computed for the hemolysis index QoI at all five flow-speed operating points. The study concluded that the medium mesh achieved GCI below 2% for all operating points and was selected as the production mesh. Detailed convergence tables and GCI calculations were compiled into a verification report.",
    "activityType": "MeshConvergenceStudy",
