      "name": "Hemolysis Index Benchmark Comparison",
      "description": "CFD-predicted hemolysis index values were compared against experimental measurements from the FDA benchmark dataset for the generic centrifugal pump. Predictions at 5 flow-speed operating points showed mean absolute error of 18% relative to experimental data. Discrepancies were attributed to uncertainty in blood rheology parameters and the simplified power-law hemolysis model. The validation result was generated from the experimental correlation activity.",
      "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/experimental-correlation-validation"
    },
    {
